CHICKENPOX - RUSSIA: (RYAZAN REGION)
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Thu 30 Apr 2009
Source: Rospotrebnadzor (Ryazan region) [translated and abbreviated
by Mod. NP, edited]
<http://www.rospotrebnadzor-rzn.ru/news/141>


Chickenpox in Ryazan region
---------------------------
A serious outbreak of chickenpox has broken out in the Ryazan region
this year [2009] and is increasing in severity. In all, 2304 cases
have been registered during the past 3 months. The incidence rate is
202.9 per 100 000 inhabitants. This rate exceeds the incidence rate
in the same period of the previous year by 47.2 percent with an
average long-term index of morbidity of 30.5 percent. 89 percent of
patients are children under 14 years old, and the remainder are
teenagers and adults.

A vaccine against chickenpox -- Varilrix -- is now available in the
Russian Federation for vaccination of children from 12 months of age,
and other vulnerable groups.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-RUS
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Further information on the origins of this severe outbreak and its
progress and outcome would be welcomed. The Ryazan region can be
located in the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at:
<http://healthmap.org/r/00bx>.
- Mod.CP]
